## Data Organization Rules

### Mock Data Files
- All mock/static data must be placed in separate files in `src/data/` directory
- Mock data files must be prefixed with "MOCK" in the filename (e.g., `MOCK-wallet-balance.ts`, `MOCK-user-data.ts`)
- Mock data should be exported as named constants with TypeScript types
- Mock data files should include comments indicating they are temporary and will be replaced with API calls

### Utility Functions
- All utility functions must be placed in separate files inside `src/utils/` directory
- Group related utilities in the same file (e.g., `currency.ts`, `address.ts`, `formatting.ts`)
- All utility functions must be pure functions with proper TypeScript types
- Common utilities like `formatCurrency`, `truncateAddress`, `formatDate` should have dedicated files
- Export utilities as named exports, not default exports


